Name: VERTICAL ORIENTATION, DEGREES
Explanation: ANGLE OF 0 TO 90 DEGREES WITH A RESOLUTION OF 1 DEGREE, SPECIFYING THE APPROXIMATE PLANAR ORIENTATION OF THE SURFACE ON WHICH THE DESIRED MEAN POINT OF IMPACT (DMPI) RESIDES RELATIVE TO THE VERTICAL (PERPENDICULAR TO THE GROUND).

Name: RUNWAY LONG AXIS ORIENTATION IN DEGREES MAGNETIC
Explanation: THE LONG AXIS OF THE RUNWAY APPROACH GIVEN IN DEGREES MAGNETIC.

Name: ZONE LONG AXIS ORIENTATION IN DEGREES MAGNETIC
Explanation: THE ORIENTATION OF THE LONG AXIS OF THE ZONE IN DEGREES MAGNETIC.

Name: LANDING SITE LONG AXIS ORIENTATION IN DEGREES MAGNETIC
